+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S7-P01-T077 (freeze six-theme visual + key-motion baseline as an un-deletable contract; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Seventy-seventh task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program; opens Stage S7 (UI/UX, Motion & Performance). Freezes the recently-restored six themes (warm/minimal/fresh/techno/cosmos/forest) and their ambience/motion layer as an UN-DELETABLE contract: a deterministic asset-hash baseline over the deployed worker's complete visual/motion surface. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; the task reads deploy/cloudflare/worker_cloud.js (the live build b189d3cc0703) plus two read-only GETs to verify the live contract, and changes no worker/production/theme code -- it only FREEZES the current state. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/visual_baseline.py: extract_contract (theme rules, THEME_NAV/FX/HERO/HERO_VIDEO mappings, CSS/HERO_CSS/THEME_JS/HEAD_INIT/FX_LAYERS surfaces, reduced-motion rule, keyframes), asset_hashes (a MASTER visual hash over the whole surface (CSS+HERO_CSS+THEME_JS+HEAD_INIT+FX_LAYERS+the hero/dashboard DOM+blurChars/sparkSVG DOM producers+the PAGE shell that injects them+the heroSection() assembly wiring+the todayPage { hero } render pass+the THEME_OPTIONS enumeration+the hero-video asset bytes+mappings) so nothing in the theme/motion identity can change without detection, plus per-theme attribution hashes over every `[data-theme]` rule + its ambience `.fx-*` motion CSS, a SEPARATE reduced-motion hash, and keyframes/fx-layers/hero-css hashes), baseline_matrix (6 themes x 6 routes x 5 viewports = 180 cells), build_baseline, detect_regression. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S7-P01-T077/: visual_baseline_manifest.json (matrix + asset hashes + screenshot/interaction-recording schema), known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND after seven HOLEs were fixed to cover the full theme/motion surface (the hero/dashboard DOM, the blurChars/sparkSVG DOM producers, the PAGE shell, the THEME_OPTIONS enumeration, the heroSection() assembly wiring, the hero-video asset bytes, the todayPage { hero } pass) and a vacuous live-check control was de-vacuoused). Acceptance verified for the machine-verifiable backbone (evidence/ADP-S7-P01-T077/test-results/visual_baseline_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the 6x6x5 matrix is complete; the six per-theme fingerprints are distinct and the coverage is not shallow (per-theme rule counts warm2/minimal7/techno7/cosmos3/forest12, ambience fx-rule counts cosmos11/minimal5/techno5); nineteen un-deletable-contract controls all flag a regression (delete a theme, mutate a token, change an fx mapping, change a hero video, change ambience-motion CSS, change a per-theme component rule, change HERO_CSS, change a keyframe, delete the hero <video>, rename the cosmos gauge arc, gut the blurChars DOM producer, recolour the sparkSVG DOM producer, remove the PAGE ${FX_LAYERS} injection, remove the PAGE ${THEME_JS} injection, delete a theme from THEME_OPTIONS, corrupt a THEME_OPTIONS key, change heroSection's return-wiring, swap a hero video's bytes, drop todayPage's { hero } pass), plus a theme-set consistency cross-check (THEMES == THEME_OPTIONS == THEME_NAV), while a benign non-visual edit does not; reduced-motion is recorded separately (own hash + recording variant, removal flagged). A live-contract check (test-results/live_contract_check.txt) confirms the live production site serves the full six-theme contract (all 6 token blocks, 4 fx layers, reduced-motion, mappings, hero videos). The final 'Owner з°ЃиЃ§еЯЇзЇњ' is a HUMAN sign-off the implementer does NOT self-sign; this package is READY_FOR_OWNER_CONFIRMATION. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0, recurring cloud 0; 2 read-only GETs. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
