 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S6-P03-T076 (full-horizon Shadow closeout + go/stop release decision; SHADOW)
 
 - Seventy-sixth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program; closes S6-P03. Aggregates the real S6-P03 shadow predictors (T074 source-silence, T075 topic-acceleration & A0->A1 diffusion) over their full rolling horizon and renders an HONEST go/stop release decision: GO (recommend showing to users) iff Brier skill is positive AND stable (every rolling window keeps positive skill -- sustained, not one lucky window), calibration is acceptable (Expected Calibration Error within tolerance), and user lead value is clear (predictions arrive early enough with positive net human value); otherwise STOP with a disable flag and the failed criteria. release_mode SHADOW; the decision is computed in the dev/shadow environment only, the production worker/cron/data untouched, 0 cloud cost, DIR-007 unaffected, and the realtime build is unchanged. IMPORTANT: a GO here is a RECOMMENDATION, not a production action -- actual user-facing rollout stays gated on the S6 Exit Owner gate; this task deploys nothing. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/horizon_shadow_closeout.py: skill_assessment (per-window + aggregate Brier skill, sustained = every window > 0), calibration_assessment (ECE as the gate metric with the worst single-bin error reported as a diagnostic only), lead_value_assessment (positive lead time AND positive net human value), release_decision (GO iff all three, else STOP + disable_flag + failed_criteria), closeout. Reuses T073 forecast_ledger (brier_skill_score, calibration); operational MODEL_SPEC untouched. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P03-T076/: horizon_shadow_closeout_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S6-P03-T076/test-results/horizon_shadow_closeout_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0), the verifier re-deriving Brier skill and ECE with its own formulas: the real shadow yields GO -- six rolling windows all keep positive Brier skill (per-window BSS 0.35/0.307/0.357/0.392/0.445/0.467, aggregate 0.387), calibration ECE 0.093 <= 0.15 (worst single bin 0.333 disclosed as a diagnostic, not the gate), and lead value is clear (90-day lead, net human value 14); and the gate is not a rubber stamp -- four degenerate shadows each flip exactly one criterion to STOP (a regressing skill window, a miscalibrated forecast, no net value, zero lead time), each with the disable flag set and the precise failed criterion. Realtime not regressed (no production deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0, recurring cloud 0 (SHADOW dev env). Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
